            "answer_text": "1 Billion years?! According to the survey made by Future Humanity institute, Oxford University, there is a 19% chance that the humanity won\u2019t survive 21st century. The chance of every human being killed by superintelligent AI is estimated to be higher than the end of our existence caused by the nuclear wars. It\u2019s estimated to be 5%. We may be digging our graves ourselves when sending signals to the space, letting everyone know that we exist. Or when we create super intelligent robots, which may get out of control. There are so many ways to end our existence and we are so unready for them even today, when we are smartest and most powerful than we have ever been, that it\u2019s a tremendous luck that we have survived till these days. My answer is about humanity, while the question was about Earth as Vatsal Rathod has kindly corrected me. But I decided to leave the answer as long as some people has found it interesting. ",
