                "href": "/profile/John-Chapman-103"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes but we probably won\u2019t, most of the larger animals probably won\u2019t and all the other life might not either. The human species and larger animals are very vulnerable to a number of extinction level events (ELE). These have happened many times in the past. You are probably aware of the one which killed the dinosaurs 65 million years ago - an impact from an Everest size rock. Other ELEs are: nearby supernovasupervolcano eruptiona rogue neutron star or mini-black hole passing - those don\u2019t have to hit.We (some of us) will probably survive a plague and an ice age. There\u2019s no chance of a waterworld scenario. Very little would survive another moon creation event - a few bacteria might survive if splashed into space. ",
